  "prompt": "How was Ankara chosen to be the capital of Turkey?",
  "response": "Ankara was chosen as the capital of Turkey in 1923, a decision influenced by several strategic, political, and symbolic factors following the establishment of the Republic of Turkey.\n\n1. **Geographical Location**: Ankara is located in the central part of Turkey, which made it more accessible from various parts of the country compared to Istanbul, the former capital. This central location was believed to facilitate better governance and communication across the nation.\n\n2. **Security Reasons**: After World War I and during the Turkish War of Independence, Istanbul was seen as vulnerable and under foreign occupation. Choosing Ankara helped establish a seat of power that was more secure from foreign influence and military threats.\n\n3. **Symbol of Modernization**: The leadership of Mustafa Kemal Atat\u00fcrk, who was determined to modernize Turkey, viewed Ankara as a symbol of a new, progressive, and secular nation. The move to Ankara was part of broader efforts to break from the Ottoman past and define a new national identity.\n\n4. **Development Potential**: Ankara was relatively small and underdeveloped at the time, which provided an opportunity for rapid growth and development as the new capital. The Turkish government invested in infrastructure, institutions, and services, facilitating the city\u2019s transformation into a modern capital.\n\n5. **Political Centralization**: By establishing a new capital in Ankara, the government aimed to reinforce a sense of national unity and promote a centralized political structure, making it easier to implement reforms across the diverse regions of Turkey.\n\nOverall, the decision to move the capital from Istanbul to Ankara was a deliberate choice to embody the aspirations of the newly founded Republic of Turkey and to signify a break from its Ottoman past.",
